rComments: Professor Ainslie's lectures are very clear (probably the clearest of any Philosophy class I've taken) and he has a good sense of humour. Be careful though, because there are only two essays and an exam -- not much chance to recover from bad marks.
A little grumpy at times but I thoroughly enjoyed his lectures. His snarky sense of humour kept me laughing. Class content was enjoyable this was one of my favourite classes.
Great prof.
Awesome lecturer. Open and helpful even though he is also the president of UC.
Great lecturer who genuinely shows an interest in the material and cares about his students. Too much use of Powerpoint though... lectures are basically able to be skipped.

Positives: funny, approachable, explains concepts clearly, does not regurgitate what's in the readings but goes beyond it, fair, uses power point... and very adorable! Negatives: could be repetitive, paper topics could have been more thought provoking, tends to go in circles when explaining things
He is a great lecturer and is pretty sexy.

he has a real passion for the material.  extensive reading list seems intimidating at first, but you can skim it because his lectures are excellent.  he has a good sense of humour, is friendly, helpful and light hearted, which is what you want friday at 9am.  you learn about the  material...and his dog.

He's wonderful. Passionate and funny.
